        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Ouachita State Park, or 12 miles northwest of Hot Springs,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs Memorial Field...     Magnet Cove...
Oaklawn Racetrack...              Mountain Pine...
Sunshine...                       Mt Tabor...
Royal...                          Lena Landing Rec Area...
Gulpha Gorge...                   Hamilton...
Hempwallace...                    Owensville...
Red Oak...                        Nance...
Crystal Springs Landing...        Jessieville...
Mountain Valley...                Lake Ouachita State Park...
Rockwell...                       Hot Springs National Park...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
